HEADWORD: nightclub
<hw>nightclub</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An establishment providing
entertainment (as singers, dancers, or comedy acts), usually open late
into the night or early morning, typically serving alcoholic beverages
and food.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cabaret.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

